The paper discusses a new dataset for Visual Question Answering (VQA), which is a task related to computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the goal of achieving human-level Artificial Intelligence (AI), which suggests cs.AI as another likely sub-category. The paper evaluates existing VQA neural models, indicating a focus on machine learning (LG) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the issue of implicit bias, which is a topic related to information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category as well.
